                ],
                "institute": "3CPRIMP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Radioactive Ion Beam Line",
                "                in Lanzhou (RIBLL)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "FRAGM"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A 16C secondary beam at about 24.0",
                "MeV/nucleon was produced from a 18O primary beam at",
                "59.6MeV/nucleon impinging on a 9Be target with a",
                "thickness of 4.5 mm. The average beam intensity and",
                "the purity of 16C were up to 1E4 particles per second",
                "and 90%, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detection of outgoing 16C and recoil",
                "protons/deuterons in coincidence."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDEG",
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The secondary beam was purified by a",
                "uniform 650-um aluminum degrader, and was identified",
                "by the time-of-flight and energy losses. The charged",
                "particles were detected and identified with standard",
                "Delta E-E methods."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 4.37 +- 0.05 mg/cm2 (CH2)n target was used to",
                "measure the protons scattering data.",
                "A 9.53 +- 0.12 mg/cm2 (CD2)n target were used to",
                "measure the deuterons scattering data.",
                "A 13.73 +-0.13 mg/cm2 carbon target was employed to",
                "subtract the background coming from carbon atoms in",
                "the (CH2)n and (CD2)n targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three PPACs were installed upstream of targets",
                "to provide beam tracking information, with a",
                "resolution of the hit position on the target less",
                "than 1.0 mm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A set of double-sided annular",
                "silicon strip detector (DSSD) and five telescopes (T0,",
                "T1UP, T1DOWN, T2UP, T2DOWN) were used to detect",
                "and identify the charged particles. T0 and T2 were",
                "employed to detect the elastic and inelastic",
                "scattering channels. The telescope T0 consists of",
                "three 1000-um-thick DSSDs, three 1500-um-thick",
                "large-surface silicon detectors (SSDs), and a layer of",
                "4-cm-thick CsI(Tl) crystals. The telescope T2 was",
                "composed of a 300-um-thick DSSD, a 1500-um-thick SSD,",
                "and a layer of CsI(Tl) crystals. other telescopes were",
                "employed to detect transfer reaction channels."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
